annotationA: Fork head is a winged-helix nuclear transcription factor most studied for its role in salivary gland formation, where it is required for salivary gland viability, invagination, and maintaining expression of other early-expressed salivary gland transcription factors. It works with sage to activate expression of salivary gland specific gene products, such as secreted proteins and their modifying enzymes
annotationB: ATP binding; protein binding; ribosomal protein S6 kinase activity; protein serine/threonine kinase activity
